  "text": "Cell Viability and Enzyme Activities. On each day, samples were taken for substrate depletion, and cultures incubated with the same concentration of tolbutamide (225 M) were tested for viability and biotransformation capacities. Cell viability was determined by trypan blue exclusion. Testosterone hydroxylation activity was determined according to the method of [CITATION_1] . Cytosolic protein was used to estimate cell number and measured according to [CITATION_2] using bovine serum albumin as a standard.",
